  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps that help you find recipes based on the ingredients you have on hand:\n\n1. Supercook\n- Free app\n- Enter ingredients you have\n- Provides recipes from multiple websites\n- Filters by cuisine, diet, etc.\n\n2. Yummly\n- Personalized recipe suggestions\n- Ingredient search function\n- Can save and organize recipes\n- Dietary preference filters\n\n3. AllRecipes Dinner Spinner\n- Search recipes by ingredients\n- Categorize by type of meal\n- Filter by dietary needs\n- Free app\n\n4. BigOven\n- Large recipe database\n- \"Use Up Leftovers\" feature\n- Can input ingredients\n- Suggests recipes based on available items\n\n5. Spoonful\n- Focuses on using ingredients you have\n- Suggests recipes with minimal additional shopping\n- Easy ingredient input\n\n6. MyFridgeFood\n- Simple, straightforward website/app\n- Enter ingredients\n- Generates recipe options\n- Very user-friendly\n\nMost of these apps are available on iOS and Android and offer free versions with optional paid upgrades. They can help reduce food waste and make meal planning easier by using ingredients you already have.",
